{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"20873ceb-4e50-4e43-bf54-fbc6095144a6","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LT9iVegxup4tcarJi7L2xf","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"262784a7-fca0-43c4-bc33-25a9e92f5c26","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. For .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, you need to set specific environment variables\n2. For Kubernetes, they need pod spec changes (env vars, volume mounts for dump storage)\n\nKey environment variables for .NET crash dump collection:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables crash dumps\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - enable diagnostics for createdump\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, the crash dump support relies on `createdump`, and the environment variables work similarly to regular .NET apps, though the mechanism is slightly different since NativeAOT is ahead-of-time compiled.\n\nThe critical difference for NativeAOT is that `createdump` isn't bundled with the runtime, so I need to specify its location via `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`. I should also set up a volume for storing the dumps and ensure the security context includes the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so the process can actually generate the dumps. The `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` pattern should include something like `%d` for unique identifiers across multiple crashes.","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"DA08:2F4A2A:22FDEF4:26B6960:6A03D8B4"},"id":"7f3a276e-0b94-46f1-9ebc-62e6a507e695","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:49:56.873Z","parentId":"6aa535de-b920-4a6a-bb4c-96fc1ccb8ed5"}
