{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4129297d-09db-433b-a53d-ec468ad9b1e5","content":"Here's what you need for NativeAOT crash dump collection:\n\n**Environment variables** — tell the runtime to invoke `createdump` on crash:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # 1=Mini 2=Heap 3=Triage 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/coredump.%d.%t\"      # %d=PID %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"       # required for NativeAOT (no bundled runtime)\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — volume for dumps + `SYS_PTRACE` so `createdump` can attach:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... image, ports, etc.\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi        # tune to your expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is mandatory for NativeAOT since `createdump` isn't bundled with the runtime.\n- `SYS_PTRACE` is required — without it, `createdump` can't read process memory.\n- `emptyDir` is fine for transient collection; swap to a PVC if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Use `%d` (PID) and `%t` (timestamp) in the dump name to avoid overwrites on repeated crashes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"262784a7-fca0-43c4-bc33-25a9e92f5c26","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"DA12:F4466:233734D:26F0165:6A03D8C3"},"id":"06efc0d9-a11d-4b79-b0ed-acd51097473a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:50:07.772Z","parentId":"82a59e96-9701-4aca-8716-5e382c53d42b"}
